sql:
SELECT AVG(c.annual_income) AS avg_annual_income, MAX(c.annual_income) AS max_annual_income
FROM customers c
INNER JOIN customer_feedback cf ON c.customer_id = cf.customer_id;

external_knowledge:
- Customer satisfaction ratings are based on a scale of 1-10; 
- The claim priority indicates the order in which claims should be addressed, based on their count; 
- Satisfaction quartiles divide customers into four equal groups based on their average satisfaction ratings, providing a relative measure of their satisfaction compared to others.
